Introduction

Doo Ri is a South Korean singer and model under ProBeat Company. She is a member and the main singer of the girl group GBB and a former and is also a former member of Sol-T.
Doori was in a car accident on May 2, 2018 while on her way to get makeup done, but did not have serious injuries.

She recorded the OST “Can’t We Please, Love” for the drama “Vogue Mom” in 2017. She made her official solo debut in 2018.

In February 2019, she joined the competitive survival reality show Miss Trot and won, earning her a place in the trot-pop girl group Venus which debuted on August 6, 2019. She was the MC of Drone Soccer: Striker in the Sky in 2019, and she sang a soundtrack for "Home for Summer" the same year.
